cs.SC, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SY, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of a computer algebra system (Maxima) for computations involving Clifford algebras. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper introduces two new packages for Maxima related to Clifford algebras. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper discusses the use of computational tools for automating calculations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper discusses the applications of Clifford algebras in engineering. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the paper uses geometric algebra as a computational model.
